post_text: Great day to be a Hornet! Girls A-Team battled Fairview to a 1-1 TIE after 12 grueling innings! Boys A-Team came back from a 6-1 deficit to win with a walk-off single by Parker Bell for a 9-8 win! Winning pitcher was also Parker Bell! Both B-Teams played, learned, and got some experience under their belts to help them for games this Friday vs Howell Valley. Good job to all and GOOOOOOO HORNETS!

post_text:
YOUR HELP IS NEEDED! We are currently in need of some baseball and softball equipment. Any former Hornets or anyone who may have some lightly used gear laying around and would like to donate it to a great cause, it would be greatly appreciated! Before we spend the high dollar amount for new equipment we wanted to first check with our amazing community for any donations of the following:

Softball bats, catcher’s gear. pitcher’s safety masks, batting helmets with face mask or any other equipment that we might need.

Baseball bats, catcher’s gear, helmets, and catcher’s mitts.

If you or someone you know has any of this they’d be willing to donate to a good cause please comment or send us a PM! Thank you for continued support!

Tomorrow, Tuesday October 3rd, we will be taking Hornet CC members to the WPMS Invitational at the WP track facility. We will depart JH at 3:00 PM and the first race will begin at 4:00 PM. This will mean there will be NO PRACTICE for those CC members who are not going to the meet. Race schedule will be as follows (ALL TIMES ARE APPROXIMATE):

4:00 PM - 7/8 Girls 1.5 miles
4:25 PM - 7/8 Boys 1.5 miles
4:50 PM - 5/6 Girls 1.5 miles
5:10 PM - 5/6 Boys 1.5 miles
5:40 PM - 4th & Under Girls 1 mile
5:55 PM - 4th & Under Boys 1 mile

Also, note there is an entry fee of $1 for all spectators who are not students. If you have any questions feel free to contact Coach Spittler or Coach Harrill.
